            . I live at <placeName id="t18211205-76-crimeloc471">Enfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-76-crimeloc471" type="placeName" value="Enfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-76-crimeloc471" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-76-off469 t18211205-76-crimeloc471"></join>. On Wednesday night, the 17th of November, I lost a whip from the stable, and some ducks from the pond. I observed the traces of a man with high shoes, and another with low shoes. The prisoner worked on the premises three days before, and wore low shoes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-76-person920">
                  JOHN 
                  MEAD
               <interp inst="t18211205-76-person920" type="surname" value="MEAD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-76-person920" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-76-person920" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable of Enfield. On Saturday, I went and found the whip in the prisoner's room.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-76-person921">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ROSE
               <interp inst="t18211205-76-person921" type="surname" value="ROSE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-76-person921" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-76-person921" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Downing. I hung the whip in the stable, and locked it at eight o'clock, the night before; the key was kept over the door, the prisoner knew that.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I found it.</p>
